summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeLiquid Liner is a water-resistant, highly pigmented, true-matte liquid liner that glides on evenly and delivers precise lines with ease. Featuring a soft felt-tip precision applicator, this liner lets you flawlessly create everything from sharp thin lines to dramatic bold lines without skipping.
details: DetailsBenefitsLong-lasting, water-resistant, full-pigment formulaSuper-fluid, water-based gel formula glides on effortlesslyVersatile application lets you create everything from superfine lines and perfect cat-eyes to bold eyeliner looksFeaturesFormulated without parabens, gluten, phthalates, alcohol or mineral oilClinically tested and dermatologist testedItem 2551413How To UseShake well before use.With light pressure, use the felt tip applicator to create sharp, precise lines. With more pressure, use the flat side of the applicator to create bolder, thicker lines.PRO TIPS:When not in use, always keep the cap on tightly and the component standing upright (tip facing down) so product is always ready to apply.To ensure a precise application every time, wipe off the brush tip with a damp tissue to clean the brush between uses.For a winged liner look, begin by drawing the tail end, creating a line that extends from the lash line outward. Then, draw a straight line starting at the tail end toward the center of the lid. Fill in the outline. Finish by extending the liner from the center of the lid toward the inner corner.Can be used on the face and body to create detailed line work.IngredientsWater/Aqua/Eau, Glycerin, Styrene/Acrylates Copolymer, Triethyl Citrate, Silica, Xanthan Gum, Sodium Citrate, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Lactic Acid, Benzyl Alcohol, PPG-26-Buteth-26, Sodium Dehydroacetate, Dehydroacetic Acid, Iron Oxides (CI 77499).Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

Finish by extending the liner from the center of the lid toward the inner corner.Can be used on the face and body to create detailed line work.

reviews.headline: NOT waterproof
reviews.comments: This eyeliner is marketed as a waterproof eyeliner which is what I'm always on the hunt for. This eyeliner is not at all waterproof, it swipes away with even a little bit of water. On the flip side, if you make a mistake on your eyeliner its easy to re-do after wiping it awah some water and a qtip. I will say its a nice dark, black matte eyeliner! So if you're just looking for a good black, NON-waterproof eyeliner then this could be a good pick otherwise try another eyeliner that is actually waterproof.

faceoff_positive.headline: Wig: Snatched

faceoff_negative.comments: I love how a cat eye looks on me & only use liquid liner to help me create a precise fine line with a flicked out wing. I received this liquid liner vox box complimentary in exchange for my honest opinions I was thrilled because liquid liner is a staple in my makeup bag. The new liquid liner by Anastasia Beverly Hills is formulated to be highly pigmented water-resistant with a matte finish. I have to admit that this liquid liner has a better color pay off than my current favorite liner. It does have a true black matte finish. The formulation does stay wet for a little while but once it dries down it stays put & doesn't become dry or flaky throughout the day. One difference I noticed for abh's formulation is that it is labeled as water resistant instead of water proof. What this means is that it's a water based formulation & will not withstand watery eyes crying or rainy weather which is a little problematic as far as creating a winged liner that lasts all day in certain conditions. This means that when it becomes wet this liquid liner will smudge & rub off completely so keep that in mind. Another feature of this liner is the the soft felt-tip applicator. It claims to allow you to make thin precise lines. I have to say that this applicator is not friendly to beginners as it's a long soft & thin applicator making it flexible which I find makes it hard to give you stability when attempting to draw a thin line. I personally am not a fan of this applicator compared to my favorite liquid liner because I find it harder to be precise with this long & flexible felt tip applicator. When it's not wet this formulation holds up well during the day & survived me rubbing my eyes throughout the day. Overall this is a nice vibrant matte finish liquid liner but does not replace my current favorite because it's water resistant not water proof and the applicator makes it difficult to create even thin lines. I rate it 3.0/5.0.
faceoff_negative.headline: Vibrant black true matte liner but not waterproof
